r\n<p>There is a charge for shipping a hard copy of your certificate. All charges may be subject to review.</p>\r\n<p><b>Customer Support</b></p>\r\n<p>If you have any questions, you can drop an email to customerservice@othm.org.uk</p>\r\n<p>Can I print my certificate myself?</p>\r\n<p>The dcwstudent.othm.org.uk allows you to access and view your certificate. You can download and print a copy from the preview screen. However, this is an unverified copy and will be watermarked. The QR code can be used to confirm the details on the certificate match the details in the system.</p>\r\n<p>How will I receive my certificate hard copy?</p>\r\n<p>If you are a student, please order your hard copy of the certificate at dcwstudent.othm.org.uk or contact your OTHM study centre to get the hard copy of the certificate.</p>\r\n<p>Until it is possible to provide a hard copy the Student Verification Portal allows you to access and view your certificate, to print an unverified copy, to confirm the details using the QR code and to create ‘Connections’ with third parties (employers, Universities etc) giving permission for them to log in and view your qualification to verify its authenticity. See Connections on the dashboard.</p>\r\n<p>Does my certificate look different to the example shown?</p>\r\n<p>Some browsers do not render the certificates as well as others. Your certificate may not display correctly in Microsoft Edge or Internet Explorer. We would recommend re-trying using Chrome or Firefox. If your certificate still does not look like the example then use the ‘Report’ function (yellow button) in the view documents section of the student verification portal and describe the problem. This will send a message to the Admin team and can be checked for you.</p>\r\n<p>Can I give employers/others access to verify my award?</p>\r\n<p>Yes – you can create a Connection with third parties (employers, Universities etc) giving permission for them to log in and view your qualification to verify its authenticity. See Connections on the dashboard to start. You will be asked how long you wish to allow access for. After this date Third parties will no longer be able to access your information.</p>\r\n<p>Will updating contact details on the Student Verification Portal update my details with OTHM Qualifications?</p>\r\n<p>No - Updating your contact details in the student verification portal will NOT update the core OTHM Qualifications contact details for you. If you wish to change this you can email to customerservice@othm.org.uk</p>\r\n<p>Can I get a digital transcript?</p>\r\n<p>Yes. </p>\r\n<p>I am a third party, how do I access documents to verify?</p>\r\n<p>Third parties can register for our verification portal dcwverify.othm.org.uk. Once registered you can request to create a ‘Connection’ with a portal user. If the user approves your request you will be able to view their documents for a limited time. Alternatively, you can request that a user invites you to create a connection with them. You will only be able to see the documents that the user has given permission to share with you and documents are only valid when viewed in the Verification Portal.</p>\r\n<p>Is there a charge for this service?</p>\r\n<p>Currently there is no charge to access the Student Verification Portal or the Verification Portal to view documents. Hard copy documents cannot be ordered via these services at this time. There remain charges for replacement parchments, and orders can be made via the OTHM Qualifications online shop dcwstudent.othm.org.uk. If you are a centre, you can order at dcwcentre.othm.org.uk. All charges may be subject to review.</p>\r\n<p>I still need help using the Student Verification Portal – who do I contact?</p>\r\n<p>Please refer to the user guides on the website , which demonstrates how to use the Student Verification Portal. If you still encounter problems please contact customerservice@othm.org.uk providing your email, date of birth and learner registration number.</p>\r\n<p><b>Payment Methods</b></p>\r\n<p>You can pay using your credit card or debit card. </p>\r\n<p><b>Delivery Rules</b></p>\r\n<p>The online shop displays the delivery options for the certificates and transcripts</p>\r\n<p><b>Refund policy</b></p>\r\n<p>The certificates once ordered can not be returned to the OTHM Qualifications. If there are others, it will be replaced  </p>\r\n\r\n",
  "FaqBodyThirdParty": "\r\n<p><b>eCommerce orders</b></p>\r\n<p>- New\r\n<p>If you wish to make an order for a hard copy of a certificate, please visit the OTHM Qualifications online shop at <a href=\"https://dcwstudent.othm.org.uk/\"> https://dcwstudent.othm.org.uk/ </a>. All charges may be subject to review.</p>\r\n<p><b>User Account</b></p>\r\n<p>What email address should I use to Register for the Student Verification Portal?</p>\r\n<p>You must use the email address that you registered at the time you registered with your OTHM study centre.. If you use a different email address this will delay your access to the system as your registration must be checked and approved. If you can’t remember the email address you used you can contact customerservice@othm.org.uk providing your name, date of birth and registration number.</p>\r\n<p>I haven’t received the email to confirm my email address\r\n<p>Please check your email spam and/or junk folders as your email provider may not have recognised the sender as a safe sender and re-directed it from your inbox. If after checking your spam and junk folders you still have not received your confirmation email please contact customerservice@othm.org.uk providing your name, date of birth and registration number.</p>\r\n<p>I have registered but have received a message saying that my account must be approved?\r\n<p>During the registration process your information is matched with the information held by  OTHM Qualifications for you. If any part of the information provided does not match, your account registration must be checked and approved by the OTHM Qualifications. This could take up to 2 working days at busy times. Once the account has been checked your account will be released and you will be able to log in. Please contact customerservice@othm.org.uk providing your name, date of birth and registration number if you are still unable to gain access 2 working days after initially registering.</p>\r\n<p><b>Delivery & Shipping</b></p>\r\n<p>There is a charge for shipping a hard copy of your certificate. All charges may be subject to review.</p>\r\n<p><b>Customer Support</b></p>\r\n<p>If you have any questions, you can drop an email to customerservice@othm.org.uk</p>\r\n<p>Can I print my certificate myself?</p>\r\n<p>The dcwstudent.othm.org.uk allows you to access and view your certificate. You can download and print a copy from the preview screen. However, this is an unverified copy and will be watermarked. The QR code can be used to confirm the details on the certificate match the details in the system.</p>\r\n<p>How will I receive my certificate hard copy?</p>\r\n<p>If you are a student, please order your hard copy of the certificate at dcwstudent.othm.org.uk or contact your OTHM study centre to get the hard copy of the certificate.</p>\r\n<p>Until it is possible to provide a hard copy the Student Verification Portal allows you to access and view your certificate, to print an unverified copy, to confirm the details using the QR code and to create ‘Connections’ with third parties (employers, Universities etc) giving permission for them to log in and view your qualification to verify its authenticity. See Connections on the dashboard.</p>\r\n<p>Does my certificate look different to the example shown?</p>\r\n<p>Some browsers do not render the certificates as well as others. Your certificate may not display correctly in Microsoft Edge or Internet Explorer. We would recommend re-trying using Chrome or Firefox. If your certificate still does not look like the example then use the ‘Report’ function (yellow button) in the view documents section of the student verification portal and describe the problem. This will send a message to the Admin team and can be checked for you.</p>\r\n<p>Can I give employers/others access to verify my award?</p>\r\n<p>Yes – you can create a Connection with third parties (employers, Universities etc) giving permission for them to log in and view your qualification to verify its authenticity. See Connections on the dashboard to start. You will be asked how long you wish to allow access for. After this date Third parties will no longer be able to access your information.</p>\r\n<p>Will updating contact details on the Student Verification Portal update my details with OTHM Qualifications?</p>\r\n<p>No - Updating your contact details in the student verification portal will NOT update the core OTHM Qualifications contact details for you. If you wish to change this you can email to customerservice@othm.org.uk</p>\r\n<p>Can I get a digital transcript?</p>\r\n<p>Yes. </p>\r\n<p>I am a third party, how do I access documents to verify?</p>\r\n<p>Third parties can register for our verification portal dcwverify.othm.org.uk. Once registered you can request to create a ‘Connection’ with a portal user. If the user approves your request you will be able to view their documents for a limited time. Alternatively, you can request that a user invites you to create a connection with them. You will only be able to see the documents that the user has given permission to share with you and documents are only valid when viewed in the Verification Portal.</p>\r\n<p>Is there a charge for this service?</p>\r\n<p>Currently there is no charge to access the Student Verification Portal or the Verification Portal to view documents. Hard copy documents cannot be ordered via these services at this time. There remain charges for replacement parchments, and orders can be made via the OTHM Qualifications online shop dcwstudent.othm.org.uk. If you are a centre, you can order at dcwcentre.othm.org.uk. All charges may be subject to review.</p>\r\n<p>I still need help using the Student Verification Portal – who do I contact?</p>\r\n<p>Please refer to the user guides on the website , which demonstrates how to use the Student Verification Portal. If you still encounter problems please contact customerservice@othm.org.uk providing your email, date of birth and learner registration number.</p>\r\n<p><b>Payment Methods</b></p>\r\n<p>You can pay using your credit card or debit card. </p>\r\n<p><b>Delivery Rules</b></p>\r\n<p>The online shop displays the delivery options for the certificates and transcripts</p>\r\n<p><b>Refund policy</b></p>\r\n<p>The certificates once ordered can not be returned to the OTHM Qualifications. If there are others, it will be replaced  </p>\r\n\r\n",
